Properties 2.1, 2.2, and 2.3 hold by construction. The two permutation functions, p1 and p2, guarantee Prop. 2.1, for a high degree k, and Prop. 2.2. Property 2.3 is inherited from element-wise product ⊗ and circular convolution .
Properties 2.4, 2.5 and 2.6 can only be approximated. Thus, we performed tests to evaluate the appropriateness of the two considered functions.
Property 2.4 approximately holds for since approximate norm preservation already holds for circular convolution, whereas uses factor γ to preserve norm. We empirically evaluated this property. Figure 2(a) shows the average norm for the composition of an increasing number of basic vectors (i.e. vectors with unitary norm) with the two basic composition functions. Function behaves much better
than .
